Finally, $SPCE is actually a company I'm a huge fan of. Opened a position in October and plan to hold long-term...but I HAD to take advantage of the insanity of the 30% pop yesterday... so here's how this position works.

I own 257 shares of $SPCE at around $10/share. Currently up 228%

I also opened a Jan 2022 $10 Synthetic long and was paid $1,000 to open it. 

What is a synthetic long? It sounds complicated but it's not. All it is is selling puts at a certain strike price, then using that premium to buy calls at the same strike price. 

This one is up $19,000 and yesterday I sold 12 $40 calls (covered) for $4.00 collecting  $4,800 in premium (more than what my shares cost me). If $SPCE is below $40 on February 21st, I keep all of that premium and all of my shares. If it's above $40, I'll have give up my shares or cover

2/Most of what I do is long term buy and hold - if that's what you're looking for, mailchi.mp/seveninvesting/s... @7investing is the place to get those ideas.

I love me some @Stocktwits but if you want to be a successful long-term investor, I suggest ignoring 90% of the hot trade alerts in most stock feeds. For example:

$PLAN is down 10% after reporting good Q2FY20 results. The feed is going crazy with all kinds of people posting comments with no accountability. 

I'm not saying Anaplan will be a fantastic investment and we shouldn't sell. But this company is such a new IPO that the earnings call matters almost as much as the results. So take a breather, dig into the results, then decide. 

If you want to build tremendous wealth, trade less, and dive into results for yourself to come up with your own opinions. Start with Earnings releases and calls.

Last Question: Audio spend. Can you talk more about why you think Connected TV is a larger opportunity than audio, talk adoption, growth drivers, etc..

Answer: We have not given audio which includes Spotify and Pandora the attention they deserve. Audio grew by 3x for third quarter in a row which is unbelievable given how long they have been in audio.

One of the reasons I call it such a great value is that there may not be a form of advertising that captures your attention much better than audio. Way less likely to skip an ad than if you're watching Youtube or in front of a computer. More likely to give it your attention in some cases and rates are usually a fraction of the price.

So it represents a large opportunity. Growth of podcasting has been helpful and it continues to represent a huge opportunity.

$TTD Q2 19 Earnings Call Q&A Notes. Come hang in stocktwits.com/r/Founder_Le... for more on $TTD and other awesome founder-led growth companies.

Green: "Important to understand about walled-gardens. When you operate inside a walled garden (facebook, google, etc) you can't correlate attribution outside of your own site. The benefit of walled-gardens is using powerful data that isn't owned by the advertiser. You have to make sure that data never leaves the walled garden which includes closing the loop on attribution"

Can't weigh affects of advertising from inside the walled garden to outside internet, or from outside internet to inside walled-garden.

This is why it's so important for advertisers to spend on the open internet.

Connected TV will continue to grow and it will continue to be fragmented. The first place to start will be on the open-internet. Left overs will be left to walled-gardens.

THIS IS A KEY POINT FOR CTV. Gotta monitor to make sure this stays true.
